==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Newfangled
<hw>New"fan`gled</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Newly
made; of a new type or fashion; formed with the affectation of novelty;
-- sometimes used to express disapproval or disdain.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>newfangled</xex> nomenclature.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir W.
Hamilton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disposed to change; inclined to novelties; given to
new theories or fashions.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Newfangled</xex>
teachers.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>1 Tim. vi. (heading).</au>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Newfangled</xex> men.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Latimer.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Newfangledness</ent>⟦br⟧
